	<p>
	  <lb n="1"/>
	  sidhaṃ na<unclear>mo bha</unclear>gavato
	  <gap reason="lost" quantity="3" unit="character"/>
	  <unclear>vasa</unclear>raño
	  <persName key="pers:GpŚrīyajñaSātakarṇi">
	    gotami<lb n="2" break="no"/>putasa
	    araka-siriyaña-sātakaṇisa
	  </persName>
	  vasasatāya 
	  <date when-custom="27"
		datingMethod="regnal"
		datingPoint="pers:GpŚrīyajñaSātakarṇi">saṃvachara 
	        sata<unclear>vi</unclear><lb n="3" break="no"/>maṃ
	        20 + 7</date>
	  hematānaṃ pakhaṃ catuthaṃ 4 
	  di<supplied reason="lost">vasaṃ paṃca</supplied>maṃ 5
	  etiya
	  <lb n="4"/>
	  puvāya arakamahatarakena 
	  mahā<gap reason="lost" quantity="6" unit="character"/><lb n="5"/>
	  yājinā 
	  mahādaṃ<gap reason="lost" quantity="6" unit="character"/><lb n="6"/>
	  dhāya<gap reason="lost" quantity="6" unit="character"/>
        </p>
      </div>
      <div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
	<p>
	  Success! Adoration to the divine. . . va!
	  The year 
	  <date when-custom="27"
		datingPoint="pers:GpŚrīyajñaSātakarṇi"
		datingMethod="regnal">twenty-seven (20+7)</date>
	  of the existence of the power of the king, the lord
	  <persName key="pers:GpŚrīyajñaSātakarṇi">Gautamīputra 
	  Śrīyajña Sātakarṇi</persName>, the fourth (4) fortnight of summer,
	  the fifth (5) day—on the above (date) by the lord, the 
	  Mahataraka Mahā. . . a sacrificer . . . to (Bud)dha(?) . . .
	</p>
      </div>
